summary: This document is a Facebook business record produced in response to a legal request, detailing account information for a specific user. It includes metadata such as registration date, phone verification, and login history, but shows no responsive records for NCMEC cybertips, credit cards, or other financial data. The record appears to be part of investigative discovery related to the Epstein case.

keyFacts: The document is a Facebook business record for a user account, generated on December 6, 2019, covering data from January 1, 2019, to November 21, 2019.
The account was created on August 15, 2008, and was still active at the time of the record generation.
A cell phone number associated with the account was verified on December 1, 2016.
No responsive records were found for NCMEC (National Center for Missing & Exploited Children) cybertip reports associated with this account during the specified date range.

The record shows login activity from specific IP addresses on June 8, 2019, and October 20, 2019, but contains no responsive records for credit cards, PayPal, direct debit, or registered email addresses.
